Lacrimosa /lakriˈmosa/ ("tearful" in Latin and Italian) is a German symphonic metal and gothic rock band. It has been led since 1990 by Tilo Wolff, joined in 1993 by Anne Nurmi, former keyboardist of the Two Witches. It was affiliated with the dark wave movement, before moving from Satura towards a more metal and orchestral style.
